 <p><center><img src="http://user.netomia.com/kyley_eq/reignasig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/umorinkhanmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MorinkhanMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blackburrow Trainee</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/20/02 4:09:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Etheral Elixir</span><hr size=1> Well, it breaks down something like this...<br>
<br>
Whenever you're hit by a harmful non-DD spell, such as a disease dot or a curse, your character is marked with &quot;counters&quot;. A spell called &quot;Weak Poison&quot; might give you 4 poison counters, while &quot;Strong Poison&quot; might give you 10 counters.<br>
<br>
A cure-type spell is flagged to remove X number of counters. In my above example, the low-level Cure Poison spell we have might remove 5 counters. So, it would cure the weaker spell in one cast, or the stronger spell in 2 casts. On the other hand, if you used Abolish Poison, which might remove 10 counters, you could get it with one cast.<br>
<br>
For Remove Curse vs. Remove Greater Curse, it works the same way. You might have to cast RC multiple times to remove the same curse you could get with a single cast of RGC.<br>
<br>
Since most of the big mobs that have AE curses cast pretty powerful curses, it's simply a matter of time and mana efficiency to want to use RGC.<br>
<br>
An example: There are several mobs in Luclin that cast a curse called 'Balance'. Balance reduces any heals landed on the cursed player to 25% of what they should be. So a 1000hp Divine Light would actually only heal 250hp. It's a very annoying curse which usually takes two casts of RGC to remove.<br>
<br>
Therefore, when fighting a Balancing mob, you usually assign a couple of players to hit the MA with RGC immediately after they're Balanced. Sure, you could assign 4 players to do the same thing with regular RC, but it's not as efficient, and has more chances to go wrong.<br>
<br>
So, in conclusion... =P   There's nothing at all wrong with Remove Curse, it's just easier and more efficient to use RGC if you have it. =)<br>
<br>
